-- G20 committed to boosting growth: draft communique
-- 
-- Mon Jun 18, 2012 11:56am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/06/18/us-g20-communique-idUSBRE85H12N20120618

 

 LOS CABOS, Mexico  (Reuters) - The Group of 20 leaders will pledge to take all measures necessary to boost economic growth and create jobs, according to a draft communique drawn up ahead of a G20 summit. 
 "We are committed to take all the policy measures needed to strengthen demand, help global growth and restore confidence...," said the Spanish-language draft, a copy of which was obtained by Reuters. (Reporting by  Krista Hughes ; writing by  William Schomberg )